# Styling Patterns

**When styling components, use @tailwind skill for Tailwind CSS best practices, utility patterns, and responsive design guidance.**

## Tailwind CSS (Primary Method)

### Utility Classes

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Use Tailwind utility classes
<div className="flex w-full flex-col gap-6">
  <article className="mb-9">
    <Text preset="heading-1">Title</Text>
  </article>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD: Responsive classes
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
  {/* content */}
</div>
```

### ODS Theme Variables

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Use ODS CSS variables for colors
<Text
  className={clsx('text-sm', {
    'text-[--ods-color-critical-500]': hasError,
    'text-[--ods-color-primary-500]': isActive,
  })}
>
  Content
</Text>

// ✅ GOOD: Background colors with ODS variables
<div className="bg-[--ods-color-neutral-100] hover:bg-[--ods-color-primary-100]">
  Content
</div>
```

